WEBVTT

00:08.426 --> 00:10.898
Not our decision,
boss. Wish it was.

00:10.899 --> 00:13.066
When's this gonna happen?

00:13.135 --> 00:15.435
Parole board meets Monday.

00:17.840 --> 00:19.773
He killed a cop.

00:19.842 --> 00:21.508
Preaching to the choir here.

00:21.577 --> 00:23.810
But it was in 1978,
so when he was sentenced...

00:23.879 --> 00:25.812
And life without parole
was not an option.

00:25.881 --> 00:28.248
But I also know the parole board

00:28.317 --> 00:29.983
can choose
to do the right thing:

00:30.052 --> 00:33.620
honor our fallen officer
and deny him parole.

00:33.689 --> 00:35.800
Fact remains, though, they have
the authority to release him.

00:35.824 --> 00:37.457
That's a fact?
That's a travesty.

00:37.526 --> 00:40.660
This guy Terrence Dean's
been denied parole before.

00:40.729 --> 00:41.995
What changed this time?

00:42.064 --> 00:44.030
Board membership's shifted
the past two years.

00:44.099 --> 00:46.199
More violent felons are
being granted parole.

00:46.268 --> 00:48.435
Tell me about it.

00:48.504 --> 00:52.639
And our murdered cop has a son
on the job, am I right?

00:52.708 --> 00:55.675
Scott Fuller.
Detective in the 3-5.

00:55.744 --> 00:57.310
You know him?

00:57.379 --> 00:59.780
Served in the same
house for ten years.

00:59.848 --> 01:01.448
(SIGHS)

01:01.517 --> 01:02.783
Bring him in.

01:02.851 --> 01:05.285
He should hear it from me.

01:09.658 --> 01:11.358
Scott and I got a history, boss.

01:11.426 --> 01:13.760
Maybe it's better
coming from me.

01:14.863 --> 01:16.930
I'm not sure any messenger

01:16.999 --> 01:19.933
could make this news
land any easier.

01:22.037 --> 01:23.937
(SIGHS)

01:25.040 --> 01:26.439
Police Explorers?

01:26.508 --> 01:28.975
It's a youth mentoring program
sponsored by the department.

01:29.044 --> 01:31.444
I know. But how
do you find time

01:31.513 --> 01:34.181
with all the other million
things you volunteer for?

01:34.249 --> 01:37.083
You make a real connection
with these kids.

01:37.152 --> 01:39.686
They see cops as human beings.
You should try it.

01:39.755 --> 01:41.675
Be honest, most of the people
I meet on this job,

01:41.723 --> 01:43.223
I'm happy if they think
I'm a hard-ass

01:43.292 --> 01:45.959
with a short temper
and a loaded pistol.

01:46.028 --> 01:48.094
It just keeps things easier.

01:48.163 --> 01:49.996
MAN:
Somebody help me!

01:50.065 --> 01:52.165
Please! Help!

01:52.234 --> 01:54.601
Somebody help me!
Come on, come on!

01:54.670 --> 01:55.702
Okay. Let's go.

01:55.771 --> 01:56.870
Hey.

01:56.939 --> 01:58.738
Back up. Call a bus forthwith.

01:58.807 --> 02:00.125
It's 29-David to Central.

02:00.126 --> 02:00.751
What's going on?

02:00.775 --> 02:04.030
My little girl started coughing,
and then she stopped breathing.

02:04.031 --> 02:05.790
- Does she have any medical conditions?
- No.

02:05.814 --> 02:06.913
- Allergies?
- No.

02:06.982 --> 02:08.014
Oh, my God. Breathe.

02:08.083 --> 02:09.282
Did she eat anything?

02:09.351 --> 02:10.883
Y-Yeah, she had a bag of grapes.

02:10.953 --> 02:13.119
MAN 2:
Somebody's got to do something.

02:13.188 --> 02:14.721
MAN:
Does anyone know CPR?

02:14.790 --> 02:15.262
Okay.

02:15.286 --> 02:17.158
Back up. Back up.
Give her some space.

02:17.159 --> 02:19.392
I need you to back up.
Please give some space. Back up.

02:19.461 --> 02:21.161
WOMAN:
Is there anything we can do?

02:22.531 --> 02:24.431
(GIRL COUGHS)

02:28.103 --> 02:29.035
Okay.

02:29.104 --> 02:30.403
She's still not breathing.

02:30.472 --> 02:31.638
Come on, sweetheart.

02:31.707 --> 02:32.707
Come on, baby.

02:34.743 --> 02:36.776
(CRYING)

02:36.845 --> 02:39.880
Oh.

02:42.017 --> 02:43.817
All right. Okay.

02:43.886 --> 02:45.652
Where's the father?

02:45.721 --> 02:47.387
He was right here.

02:48.490 --> 02:49.789
Hey, folks!

02:49.858 --> 02:51.691
Anyone see this child's father?

02:51.760 --> 02:52.971
WOMAN: I-I don't know, Officer.
I don't see him.

02:52.995 --> 02:54.327
Anyone see him?

02:54.396 --> 02:56.563
- Come on, anyone see him?
-Where...?

02:57.666 --> 02:59.332
Looks like he took off.

02:59.401 --> 03:01.334
What the hell?

03:01.403 --> 03:04.738
(BABY CRYING)

03:06.000 --> 03:12.074
