03:13.515 --> 03:16.316
Pear salad okay?

03:16.385 --> 03:17.784
Fine.

03:17.853 --> 03:19.519
You mean fine
for a pear salad.

03:19.588 --> 03:21.254
You should've
ordered the veal.

03:21.323 --> 03:22.956
I'm just not very hungry.

03:25.060 --> 03:27.928
You read the draft of the
crime bill my office sent over?

03:27.996 --> 03:28.996
I did.

03:29.031 --> 03:30.463
So, what do you think?

03:30.532 --> 03:35.835
It's very... comprehensive.

03:35.904 --> 03:38.104
There's a lot in it.

03:38.173 --> 03:41.441
More to the point, what
will your old man think?

03:42.544 --> 03:43.710
Honestly?

03:43.779 --> 03:46.313
No, lie to me.

03:47.416 --> 03:48.815
For one thing,

03:48.884 --> 03:51.384
the bill grants state police
equal authority

03:51.453 --> 03:54.120
in the NYPD
anti-terror protocols.

03:54.189 --> 03:55.288
So?

03:55.289 --> 03:57.793
So that could blur
the lines of authority.

03:57.829 --> 03:59.328
It's a dangerous world.

03:59.380 --> 04:01.864
Adding my guys would
only make the city safer.

04:01.916 --> 04:04.550
I'm not sure the PC
would see it that way.

04:08.139 --> 04:10.279
You and I, we have
an arrangement.

04:10.303 --> 04:11.123
I know.

04:11.147 --> 04:13.760
You wanted a new sex-trafficking
law, and I got it for you.

04:13.761 --> 04:15.155
You didn't get it
for me. You got it

04:15.179 --> 04:16.457
for the thousands
of victims that were...

04:16.481 --> 04:18.231
And in return,

04:18.315 --> 04:21.017
you promised me the PC's
support for my crime bill.

04:22.270 --> 04:26.188
And I'm just saying that
that might be a problem.

04:27.325 --> 04:30.860
Your promise. Your problem.

04:38.953 --> 04:42.088
What points to it being
this guy's doing all of them?

04:42.173 --> 04:44.457
Same MO. He robs
people at gunpoint

04:44.542 --> 04:46.425
after they hit
the ATM machine.

04:46.511 --> 04:47.677
Then he delivers a beatdown.

04:47.712 --> 04:49.262
It's like a calling card.

04:49.347 --> 04:50.880
Like the mark of Zorro.

04:50.932 --> 04:52.632
But this is the fifth
tip we've gotten

04:52.717 --> 04:54.361
off of this sketch,
and they've all been dead ends.

04:54.385 --> 04:56.282
I just feel like
we're spinning our wheels.

04:56.283 --> 04:58.271
I know.
Let's just keep looking.

04:58.356 --> 04:59.605
(SIGHS)

05:01.559 --> 05:03.559
Hello.

05:06.614 --> 05:07.730
Could be.

05:07.782 --> 05:09.398
Only one way to find out.

05:14.989 --> 05:17.073
Excuse me.

05:18.076 --> 05:19.458
Hey!

05:19.544 --> 05:21.243
Hey! Police! Hold it!

05:22.163 --> 05:23.913
(PANTING)

05:26.334 --> 05:28.334
(SIREN WAILING)

05:35.226 --> 05:36.642
Move! Look out!
(SCREAMS)

05:36.728 --> 05:38.928
Move along! Come here!

05:45.737 --> 05:47.603
(BOTH GRUNTING)

05:49.357 --> 05:51.073
(PANTING)

05:51.109 --> 05:52.692
DANNY: Hey! Hey!
MAN: Get off me!

05:52.777 --> 05:54.443
- Stop moving.
- Hey!

05:54.495 --> 05:55.444
- Settle down.
- Show me your hands.

05:55.496 --> 05:56.696
DANNY:
What's your name?

05:56.781 --> 05:58.092
- Hands behind your back.
- Check his wallet.

05:58.116 --> 05:59.116
(MAN GRUNTING)

06:00.868 --> 06:03.336
Rivers, Damon.
All right, Rivers, Damon.

06:03.421 --> 06:05.538
We're gonna take
a ride downtown.

06:05.623 --> 06:06.655
(GRUNTS)
Settle down.

06:06.708 --> 06:07.708
Jackass.

06:07.759 --> 06:09.041
Come on.

06:09.127 --> 06:11.043
Good job.

