06:41.040 --> 06:42.282
So, the baby's gonna be okay?

06:42.283 --> 06:45.034
Portable chest X-ray
and ABG are normal.

06:45.119 --> 06:46.827
Pediatric neurologist
will take a look,

06:46.828 --> 06:49.162
but I think she'll be just fine
thanks to you guys.

06:49.497 --> 06:51.798
You should've seen her.
She could work here.

06:51.833 --> 06:53.199
Y-Yeah, no.

06:53.251 --> 06:55.201
Have you located
the parents yet?

06:55.253 --> 06:57.370
Not yet. We'll contact
Children's Services.

06:57.422 --> 06:58.721
Okay. Keep me posted.

06:58.807 --> 07:00.089
You want to see her?

07:00.175 --> 07:01.819
- No, we should probably get back.
- That would be great.

07:01.843 --> 07:03.760
Come on, she's right over here.

07:03.845 --> 07:05.762
(BABY CRYING)

07:09.517 --> 07:12.268
She's okay.
Just won't stop crying.

07:12.354 --> 07:14.354
Let the hero give it a try.

07:18.860 --> 07:20.943
Hey.

07:21.029 --> 07:23.746
Yeah. Okay.

07:23.832 --> 07:25.948
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

07:26.034 --> 07:28.067
Okay.

07:28.119 --> 07:30.286
Remember me?
(BABY STOPS CRYING)

07:30.372 --> 07:32.789
Wow. You're a baby whisperer.

07:32.874 --> 07:34.924
She's just scared.

07:35.010 --> 07:36.626
Who wouldn't be?

07:36.711 --> 07:38.678
Hey.

07:38.713 --> 07:41.714
Yeah. Hi.

07:41.766 --> 07:43.933
Everything's gonna be okay.

07:44.019 --> 07:45.885
Yeah.

07:45.937 --> 07:48.888
Really appreciate you
coming down here, Mr. Martinez,

07:48.940 --> 07:50.773
especially with all
you've been through.

07:50.859 --> 07:53.276
My wife told me not to
use the ATM at night,

07:53.361 --> 07:55.728
so on top of everything,
I got "I told you so's."

07:55.780 --> 07:58.114
Look, it's not your fault
what happened, okay?

07:58.199 --> 08:00.266
This is a very bad guy
we're talking about,

08:00.318 --> 08:01.701
and, uh, hopefully
with your help,

08:01.736 --> 08:03.319
this won't happen
to anyone else.

08:03.405 --> 08:05.905
He won't be able
to see me, right?

08:05.957 --> 08:07.623
No. No, absolutely not.

08:07.709 --> 08:09.492
Can I have a minute,
Detective?

08:09.577 --> 08:12.495
Yeah. Uh, one second, okay?

08:13.915 --> 08:15.548
I notified the 2-7 squad.

08:15.583 --> 08:17.633
They're sending over
Detective Kelso and a sergeant

08:17.719 --> 08:18.835
to run the lineup.

08:18.920 --> 08:20.837
Well, Kelso's a hard-ass
with a big mouth.

08:20.922 --> 08:22.088
Well, look,

08:22.140 --> 08:23.567
our vic's been through
enough already, okay?

08:23.591 --> 08:24.702
Let's just run it ourselves.

08:24.726 --> 08:26.342
Danny.
Just saying.

08:26.428 --> 08:28.511
We lose this ID,
then we're back to square one.

08:28.596 --> 08:30.263
All right?
I'm not gonna let that happen.

08:30.315 --> 08:31.431
I got it.

08:32.517 --> 08:34.633
All right, you ready?

08:34.686 --> 08:36.102
Yeah, I guess so.

08:38.690 --> 08:41.240
Stand right there,
Mr. Martinez.

08:41.275 --> 08:43.241
(EXHALES)

08:44.779 --> 08:47.413
When I open the blind,
there will be six individuals

08:47.449 --> 08:49.665
standing on the other side.
None of them can see you.

08:49.751 --> 08:51.167
Okay?

08:53.121 --> 08:54.837
(EXHALES)
Okay.

08:54.923 --> 08:56.339
Take your time.

08:56.424 --> 08:57.707
Take a look at each one of them.

08:57.792 --> 08:59.459
Let me know
if you recognize any of them.

09:07.469 --> 09:08.851
Number three.

09:08.937 --> 09:10.002
DANNY:
Number three.

09:10.054 --> 09:11.337
Where do you recognize

09:11.389 --> 09:12.389
number three from?

09:12.474 --> 09:14.140
The other night.

09:14.192 --> 09:16.675
The ATM.

09:16.728 --> 09:19.195
That's the animal robbed
and beat me.

09:21.733 --> 09:24.200
(DANNY SIGHS)

09:26.321 --> 09:28.571
Hey, Scotty. I got you.

09:28.656 --> 09:30.267
- Great to see you, Sid.
- (CHUCKLES): Hey.

09:30.291 --> 09:31.991
You, too, Scott.
(LAUGHS)

09:32.043 --> 09:34.794
Man, now, this place brings
back a lot of memories.

09:34.829 --> 09:36.695
Well, if you can remember

09:36.748 --> 09:38.915
those nights,
you weren't doing them right.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.083
(BOTH LAUGH)

09:41.169 --> 09:45.421
So, um, I don't get a lot
of calls from One PP.

09:45.507 --> 09:49.425
Yeah, well, this is one
I wish I didn't have to make.

09:51.012 --> 09:53.396
It looks like Terrence Dean's
gonna get paroled next week.

09:57.068 --> 09:59.018
How's that possible?

09:59.070 --> 10:00.570
We asked the same thing.

10:00.655 --> 10:03.389
The commissioner's not happy.
He wants you to know that.

10:03.441 --> 10:05.608
Dean handed my family
a life sentence

10:05.693 --> 10:07.827
when he killed my father.
Now he's gonna walk?

10:07.862 --> 10:09.162
Listen, Scott,
you know the deal.

10:09.197 --> 10:10.696
The parole board
calls the shots.

10:10.748 --> 10:11.948
There's nothing we can do.

10:12.033 --> 10:14.617
Who's "we"?
The PC, the NYPD.

10:14.702 --> 10:16.919
Officially, as a whole?

10:17.005 --> 10:19.922
Well, yeah, sorry to say.

10:20.008 --> 10:23.509
Or any individual officer
of the NYPD,

10:23.545 --> 10:26.212
officially or unofficially.

10:26.264 --> 10:27.913
Wouldn't be anything
official about it.

10:27.966 --> 10:29.465
Purely personal.

10:29.551 --> 10:30.600
Nah, don't go there.

10:30.685 --> 10:32.802
If this bastard killed
your old man, Sid,

10:32.887 --> 10:34.637
what would you do?

10:35.723 --> 10:37.223
Exactly.

10:37.275 --> 10:38.891
Listen, Scott,

10:38.943 --> 10:40.309
you got dealt a bum hand,

10:40.395 --> 10:42.478
but you built
a hell of a life.

10:42.564 --> 10:44.597
Janet, the kids.

10:44.649 --> 10:46.432
You don't want
to throw all that away

10:46.484 --> 10:47.900
just to settle an old score.

10:47.952 --> 10:50.286
My mom just turned 76.

10:52.207 --> 10:55.825
Spent the past
40 years alone.

10:55.910 --> 10:58.944
Dean walks out of prison
after all this time...

10:58.997 --> 11:01.497
it's only right he gets
a welcoming committee.

11:01.583 --> 11:02.123
Scott...

11:02.147 --> 11:03.584
Oh, thanks for
the heads-up, Sid.

11:03.585 --> 11:04.617
Don't worry.

11:04.669 --> 11:06.619
I'm just talkin'.

11:06.671 --> 11:08.337
Didn't sound that way.

11:08.423 --> 11:11.007
Let justice prevail.

11:12.343 --> 11:14.677
If I had a motto...

11:14.762 --> 11:17.346
that'd be it.

11:23.855 --> 11:25.938
Heard you wanted
a word with us.

11:25.990 --> 11:28.324
Yeah. Thanks for coming down.

11:28.409 --> 11:29.942
- Mm-hmm.
- What's going on?

11:29.994 --> 11:31.777
ADA assigned
to the Damon Rivers case

11:31.829 --> 11:33.279
asked me to review the files.

11:33.331 --> 11:34.413
And?

11:34.449 --> 11:36.532
Guy's a world-class scumbag.

11:36.618 --> 11:37.950
- Mm-hmm.
- Absolutely.

11:38.002 --> 11:39.202
So I'm guessing you don't want

11:39.254 --> 11:40.836
to blow the case
over a tainted lineup.

11:40.922 --> 11:42.335
What the hell
are you talking about?

11:42.359 --> 11:42.923
Look, I get it.

11:42.924 --> 11:45.841
You got a Vic that's, uh,
scared, he's beaten up--

11:45.927 --> 11:47.843
you don't want to
take any chances.

11:47.929 --> 11:50.176
If you get it, why are you
busting our chops here?

11:50.177 --> 11:53.132
Look, you know as well as I do
an outside detective

11:53.184 --> 11:54.967
unfamiliar with the suspect
is supposed

11:55.019 --> 11:56.185
to run the lineup,

11:56.271 --> 11:58.187
so the ID's
on the up-and-up.

11:58.273 --> 12:00.339
Well, we tried

12:00.391 --> 12:01.941
to get an outside detective.

12:01.976 --> 12:03.392
Weren't any available.

12:03.478 --> 12:05.194
Not according to
Detective Kelso.

12:05.280 --> 12:06.562
Well, screw Detective Kelso.

12:06.648 --> 12:08.013
Well, now the
ADA is worried

12:08.066 --> 12:09.565
about proceeding
based on this ID.

12:09.651 --> 12:11.651
Yeah, because you
opened your mouth.

12:11.703 --> 12:13.235
Also, you stuck him
in position three

12:13.321 --> 12:15.371
without giving him
a choice of where to stand.

12:15.456 --> 12:17.022
(CHUCKLES):
He could have moved.

12:17.075 --> 12:18.240
You never told him that.

12:18.326 --> 12:21.410
And everyone, including
Rivers' attorney,

12:21.496 --> 12:23.557
knows that position three is
chosen more than any other.

12:23.581 --> 12:25.464
Okay, look, Rivers is
our guy, all right?

12:25.500 --> 12:27.583
You have any other witnesses
could ID this perp?

12:27.669 --> 12:29.868
No. And this is
our best chance to get him.

12:29.921 --> 12:32.338
The ID's good. We stand by it.

12:43.985 --> 12:46.018
How'd you get
your hands on this?

12:46.070 --> 12:47.603
Governor's office
sent it over.

12:47.689 --> 12:49.054
They're testing
the waters.

12:49.107 --> 12:50.156
Not  <i>these</i> waters.

12:50.191 --> 12:51.741
That's the first time
I've seen it.

12:51.826 --> 12:54.193
I'm sure that was
just an oversight.

12:54.245 --> 12:56.495
Erin... the guy pays
as much attention

12:56.531 --> 12:59.749
to who he leaves out
as who he invites in.

12:59.834 --> 13:03.402
I do think there are some
decent proposals in there.

13:03.454 --> 13:05.955
All of which benefit
Mendez politically.

13:06.040 --> 13:08.407
Well, he  <i>is</i>
a politician.

13:08.459 --> 13:11.627
But he certainly is not
an expert in counterterrorism.

13:11.713 --> 13:14.296
You're concerned about
adding the state police

13:14.382 --> 13:16.265
to the emergency protocols?

13:16.351 --> 13:18.184
Under separate
command structures,

13:18.219 --> 13:20.386
it is a recipe for disaster.

13:20.438 --> 13:24.106
Any chance on bringing those
two bureaucracies together?

13:24.192 --> 13:25.891
Yeah, it's called
a clusterf...

13:29.781 --> 13:33.649
Any chance two heads
are... better than one?

13:39.407 --> 13:42.074
What is this?

13:43.711 --> 13:44.960
What?

13:45.046 --> 13:48.247
Since when are you shilling
for the governor?

13:48.299 --> 13:50.499
I'm not shilling.

13:50.585 --> 13:53.586
Well, lobbying for?

13:55.223 --> 13:57.590
A couple months ago,
I convinced the governor

13:57.642 --> 14:00.092
to push through
that sex-trafficking law.

14:00.144 --> 14:02.961
Convinced or traded for?

14:03.014 --> 14:04.313
Let me explain.

14:04.399 --> 14:06.965
You made a deal with the guy.

14:07.018 --> 14:08.684
Well, I didn't have a choice.

14:08.770 --> 14:11.470
What, did he hold a gun
to your head?

14:11.522 --> 14:13.823
You make deals every
single day, Dad.

14:13.908 --> 14:15.307
Yes. On my dime.

14:15.359 --> 14:19.111
Certainly not on someone else's,
and certainly not on yours.

14:21.199 --> 14:24.450
WILD GUESS:
you said you could lean on me

14:24.502 --> 14:26.819
to endorse the bill
sight unseen.

14:26.871 --> 14:29.038
I offered to speak with you.

14:29.123 --> 14:31.990
Erin, in his language,
that's a promise.

14:32.043 --> 14:33.876
"Promise" is too harsh
of a word.

14:33.961 --> 14:36.095
Well, "promise" is
certainly what he heard.

14:38.216 --> 14:40.132
Why didn't you just come to me?

14:42.770 --> 14:45.521
I knew you'd say no.

14:45.606 --> 14:47.506
Because?

14:47.558 --> 14:51.527
Governor Mendez.

14:51.612 --> 14:54.063
Because I know
border security with Albany

14:54.148 --> 14:56.065
is important to you.

14:56.150 --> 14:58.284
(SIGHS)
And what did you think I'd say

14:58.319 --> 15:00.018
when you came to me today?

15:00.071 --> 15:02.321
I hoped you'd listen.

15:03.574 --> 15:05.524
Well...

15:05.576 --> 15:07.626
I did listen.

15:07.662 --> 15:09.662
The answer's no.

15:15.509 --> 15:17.426
♪ ♪

15:22.599 --> 15:23.882
Give me a second.

15:25.143 --> 15:26.768
I heard you had a
meeting with the mayor.

15:26.854 --> 15:28.804
And you tracked me down.

15:28.889 --> 15:31.256
You must come
from a family of cops.

15:31.308 --> 15:32.774
Speaking of which...

15:32.860 --> 15:35.811
- I spoke with my father.
- And?

15:35.896 --> 15:38.447
I'm afraid it's a hard
no on the crime bill.

15:39.566 --> 15:41.266
I'm sorry to hear that.

15:41.318 --> 15:42.934
I bet you were, too.

15:42.986 --> 15:44.619
I really did try
to convince him.

15:44.705 --> 15:46.766
Well, it looks like you're
just gonna have to try harder.

15:46.790 --> 15:48.957
I was hoping there
would be another way

15:49.042 --> 15:50.659
that I could
support the bill.

15:50.744 --> 15:53.378
Like what? Ringing doorbells,
making the pitch?

15:53.414 --> 15:55.797
If that's what it takes.
That's not how this works.

15:55.883 --> 15:58.116
You gave me your word.

15:58.168 --> 16:00.802
And I should never have promised
my father's endorsement.

16:00.888 --> 16:02.454
And yet, you did.

16:02.506 --> 16:04.890
If the PC doesn't back my bill,

16:04.925 --> 16:07.292
I'll make sure
the entire legal community

16:07.344 --> 16:11.263
knows that your word isn't worth
the lipstick it's rolled over.

16:12.599 --> 16:14.933
I really did try
to honor this deal.

16:16.019 --> 16:17.802
This ain't horseshoes,
Counselor.

16:17.855 --> 16:19.438
Close don't cut it.

16:27.581 --> 16:29.915
Look, there is one
way out of this.

16:29.950 --> 16:32.584
The old man is a powerful guy,

16:32.619 --> 16:34.536
but he still has a boss.

16:34.621 --> 16:36.538
You want me to speak
with the mayor?

16:36.623 --> 16:37.822
Could be you.

16:37.875 --> 16:39.875
Could be someone you
know has their ear.

16:39.960 --> 16:42.461
There's a lot of good things
in my bill for the city.

16:42.513 --> 16:44.407
If the mayor tells
the PC to endorse it, he's got no choice.

16:44.431 --> 16:46.348
You clearly do not know
my father.

16:46.433 --> 16:47.883
But you do.

16:47.968 --> 16:50.135
Which is how we got here.

16:50.187 --> 16:52.137
♪﻿﻿﻿ ♪

17:01.231 --> 17:02.481
Hey.

17:02.533 --> 17:04.566
How'd it go with
Detective Fuller?

17:04.651 --> 17:06.034
Pretty much like you'd expect.

17:06.118 --> 17:07.852
He has a right
to be pissed off.

17:07.905 --> 17:09.820
- He's way more than that.
- Meaning?

17:12.409 --> 17:14.576
He made noises like
he'd go after Dean

17:14.661 --> 17:17.496
if he got out of prison.
I assume you told him

17:17.548 --> 17:18.863
that was a bad idea.

17:18.915 --> 17:19.998
I told him.

17:20.050 --> 17:21.866
- And?
- And it bounced.

17:21.919 --> 17:24.202
- Frank know this?
- Yeah.

17:24.253 --> 17:26.871
He asked if the threat
was knee-jerk or real real.

17:26.924 --> 17:28.056
And what do you think?

17:28.141 --> 17:30.208
Dean ambushed
and killed his old man,

17:30.260 --> 17:32.844
for which he got three squares
a day and his laundry done.

17:32.896 --> 17:34.179
You really need to ask?

17:35.265 --> 17:37.482
You think Fuller
can pull it off?

17:37.518 --> 17:39.100
A smart detective,
which he is,

17:39.186 --> 17:41.219
could find ten ways
to take him out

17:41.271 --> 17:43.271
without breaking a sweat

17:43.357 --> 17:45.273
or leaving a trace.
- What'd the boss say?

17:45.359 --> 17:47.725
Says he wants to pay Dean
a visit in prison, warn him

17:47.778 --> 17:50.695
about what's waiting for him
on the outside, if he gets out.

17:50.747 --> 17:52.280
He can't do that.

17:52.366 --> 17:54.010
It'll look like he's trying to
interfere in the parole process.

17:54.034 --> 17:55.345
- That's right.
- That's what I told him.

17:55.369 --> 17:56.609
- Good.
- That's why  <i>I'm</i> going.

17:56.670 --> 17:57.393
What?

17:57.417 --> 17:59.824
Dean has a right to know
his life is in danger.

18:00.040 --> 18:02.040
You don't give a damn
about his life, Sid.

18:02.092 --> 18:03.425
You just want
to intimidate him

18:03.510 --> 18:05.243
into withdrawing
his parole request.

18:05.295 --> 18:07.357
Garrett, if that's what happens,
I could live with that.

18:07.381 --> 18:08.296
No, this is wrong.

18:08.382 --> 18:10.131
Garrett, laying in wait,

18:10.217 --> 18:12.384
and killing a cop
in cold blood,

18:12.436 --> 18:15.270
which Dean did--
<i>that's</i> wrong.

18:18.725 --> 18:21.309
You don't wear the uniform,

18:21.395 --> 18:23.094
but you work
in this house.

18:23.146 --> 18:27.399
All right? You're gonna want
to be on the right side of this.

18:27.451 --> 18:29.067
(DOOR OPENS)

18:30.571 --> 18:31.953
(DOOR CLOSES)

18:33.740 --> 18:37.158
So, she's been medically
cleared for discharge?

18:37.244 --> 18:38.793
- Yes.
- And yet...

18:38.879 --> 18:41.129
Child Services is
nowhere to be found?

18:41.214 --> 18:43.415
I'm not their
dispatcher, Officer.

18:45.302 --> 18:46.618
Hey.

18:46.670 --> 18:49.588
Witten told me you came back
over here. What's up?

18:51.425 --> 18:54.476
The kid has no one watching
out for her is what's up.

18:54.561 --> 18:56.478
Who gave you that assignment?

18:56.563 --> 18:57.795
It's called a conscience.

18:57.848 --> 19:00.148
Well, we, uh,
we picked up the father.

19:00.233 --> 19:01.633
The hell is his problem?

19:01.685 --> 19:04.269
Outstanding warrant for criminal
sale of a controlled substance.

19:04.321 --> 19:06.304
You guys showed up.
He panicked.

19:06.356 --> 19:07.656
DA gonna charge him?

19:07.741 --> 19:08.823
Looks that way, yeah.

19:09.943 --> 19:11.860
Any word on the mother?

19:11.945 --> 19:14.996
Yeah. She's on her third round
of court-ordered rehab, upstate.

19:17.084 --> 19:18.617
(SIGHS)

19:21.922 --> 19:23.872
Poor kid.

19:23.957 --> 19:25.624
You remember anything

19:25.676 --> 19:27.175
from before you could walk?

19:27.260 --> 19:28.326
No.

19:28.378 --> 19:29.544
There you go.

19:29.630 --> 19:31.996
She's not just
a blank slate, Jamie.

19:32.049 --> 19:34.215
Come on. I'll
buy you a drink.

19:34.301 --> 19:35.383
You go ahead.

19:35.469 --> 19:37.469
Eddie, I think you
should let this one go.

19:38.605 --> 19:40.055
You go ahead.

19:40.140 --> 19:43.341
I-I'll leave as soon
as Child Services shows up.

19:43.393 --> 19:45.360
Till then...

19:45.445 --> 19:47.278
I got her back.

19:49.366 --> 19:51.533
Want anything from
the soda machine?

19:52.653 --> 19:54.569
Ginger ale if they got it.

19:54.655 --> 19:56.404
Coming right up.

19:57.708 --> 19:59.658
♪﻿﻿﻿ ♪

20:08.251 --> 20:09.751
You're new to this game.

20:09.836 --> 20:12.537
Your dad and the governor
are old pros. I mean,

20:12.589 --> 20:13.972
it just, it takes time.

20:14.007 --> 20:16.057
I don't know how much
time I have left.

20:16.143 --> 20:18.393
You feeling sorry
for yourself?

20:18.478 --> 20:20.979
The most powerful man in
New York just threatened

20:21.014 --> 20:22.347
to ruin my career.

20:22.399 --> 20:24.099
Yeah, I think I'm entitled.

20:24.184 --> 20:25.934
Erin, you decided to play ball.

20:26.019 --> 20:27.986
(CHUCKLES): Politics is
a contact sport.

20:28.021 --> 20:30.054
I was trying to do
something good.

20:30.107 --> 20:31.523
You did. But the rub is,

20:31.575 --> 20:33.408
sometimes you have
to pay the price

20:33.493 --> 20:34.859
for doing the right thing.

20:34.911 --> 20:36.561
Oh, now you tell me.

20:36.613 --> 20:39.414
THE QUESTION IS:
was it worth it?

20:43.503 --> 20:46.104
- Yeah, it was.
- Good.

20:46.173 --> 20:48.239
So the juice was
worth the squeeze.

20:48.308 --> 20:49.574
So quit bitching.

20:49.643 --> 20:51.776
Everything worthwhile
comes at a cost.

20:51.845 --> 20:54.212
Just didn't think the cost
was gonna be my reputation.

20:54.264 --> 20:55.747
Your reputation for what?

20:55.799 --> 20:57.632
For keeping promises.

20:57.718 --> 21:02.387
You promised underage sex crime
victims you'd protect them.

21:02.439 --> 21:03.555
Yeah.

21:03.607 --> 21:04.607
And did you?

21:04.641 --> 21:06.107
Yeah.

21:06.193 --> 21:10.645
Then stake your reputation
on that.

21:19.239 --> 21:20.622
- Want to grab a bite?
- Can't.

21:20.707 --> 21:22.774
My son Sean's cooking dinner
tonight.

21:22.826 --> 21:23.958
Is that a good thing?

21:24.044 --> 21:26.461
No. You're welcome to join me,

21:26.546 --> 21:28.780
though I'd strongly
recommend against it.

21:28.832 --> 21:31.166
I appreciate the warning.

21:31.251 --> 21:32.717
You got a visitor, Detectives.

21:33.837 --> 21:35.920
Mr. Martinez,
how are you doing?

21:35.972 --> 21:38.623
A little better. I heard they
charged the guy who attacked me.

21:38.675 --> 21:40.458
Well, thanks to your
cooperation, yeah.

21:40.510 --> 21:42.343
My wife made this for you.

21:42.429 --> 21:43.478
She didn't have
to do that.

21:43.563 --> 21:44.679
You'll be glad she did.

21:44.765 --> 21:46.514
Rosie's paella is legendary.

21:46.600 --> 21:47.744
Yeah, it looks good.
(PHONE RINGING)

21:47.768 --> 21:49.408
We wanted you to know
how grateful we are.

21:49.436 --> 21:51.469
- Well, we're just doing our jobs.
- Baez.

21:51.521 --> 21:52.882
But please
tell your wife thank you,

21:52.906 --> 21:54.634
'cause she just saved me
from having to eat my son's

21:54.658 --> 21:56.941
macaroni and cheese
casserole. See ya.

21:56.993 --> 22:00.528
Can I take this home?
(SIGHS)

22:00.614 --> 22:02.197
What?

22:02.282 --> 22:04.199
We've got a problem.

22:04.284 --> 22:07.035
♪﻿﻿﻿ ♪

22:07.120 --> 22:09.654
Hey. Don't shoot the messenger.

22:09.706 --> 22:11.372
Oh, trust me,
I'm thinking about it.

22:11.458 --> 22:14.008
Defense counsel filed
a motion for a Wade Hearing

22:14.094 --> 22:15.493
and the judge tossed your ID.

22:15.545 --> 22:17.712
And the ADA went
along with it?

22:17.798 --> 22:20.381
She conceded that the ID
was unduly suggestive.

22:20.467 --> 22:21.833
Yeah, because you
told her it was.

22:21.885 --> 22:23.112
- I tried to warn you.
- You didn't warn me

22:23.136 --> 22:24.636
you were gonna sell us out.

22:24.688 --> 22:26.170
I did my job.
You should try it.

22:26.223 --> 22:29.057
My job is keeping scumbags
like Rivers off the street.

22:29.142 --> 22:30.725
I don't know what the hell
your job is.

22:30.811 --> 22:32.677
Ask your sister.
Maybe you'll learn something.

22:32.729 --> 22:34.729
Typical square badge.

22:34.815 --> 22:36.147
What did you call me?

22:36.199 --> 22:38.733
I called you a square badge.

22:38.819 --> 22:40.596
What? Meaning that I'm not
a real cop like you?

22:40.620 --> 22:41.931
- You said it, not me.
- I was a real cop

22:41.955 --> 22:43.521
when you were still
in high school.

22:43.573 --> 22:44.873
And never once did I try

22:44.958 --> 22:47.125
to pin my screw-ups
on a fellow cop.

22:47.160 --> 22:48.409
Rivers is our guy,

22:48.495 --> 22:49.939
and now, thanks to you,
back on the street.

22:49.963 --> 22:52.497
No, where you put him.
And it's only a matter of time

22:52.549 --> 22:55.083
before he kills someone,
and when he does, it's on you.

22:55.168 --> 22:56.968
The hell it is.

23:03.638 --> 23:07.480
Come on, Francis, all the
firepower at this table,

23:07.481 --> 23:08.592
all the chits we
have out there...

23:08.616 --> 23:09.698
It's a parole board, Pop.

23:09.784 --> 23:11.183
They're pretty much untouchable.

23:11.235 --> 23:13.018
No one's untouchable.

23:13.070 --> 23:15.353
And Terrence Dean belongs
in prison.

23:15.406 --> 23:17.823
That's all we'd be asking them
to ensure.

23:17.875 --> 23:21.543
What you're asking is the
equivalent of jury tampering.

23:21.629 --> 23:22.889
HENRY: Call it what you want,
I don't care.

23:22.913 --> 23:24.379
He killed a cop.

23:24.465 --> 23:26.832
He should get life imprisonment.
End of story.

23:26.884 --> 23:28.050
Amen.

23:28.135 --> 23:29.051
<i>Times</i> ran an article yesterday

23:29.136 --> 23:30.169
detailing the incident.

23:30.221 --> 23:32.387
Dean made the bogus 911 call,

23:32.473 --> 23:34.039
he laid in wait
and he ambushed Fuller.

23:34.091 --> 23:35.891
He never had a chance.

23:35.976 --> 23:37.296
HENRY: Mm.
DANNY: I'm with Gramps.

23:37.344 --> 23:39.156
Terrence Dean should spend
the rest of his life rotting

23:39.180 --> 23:41.897
in prison and so should
anybody else who kills a cop.

23:41.982 --> 23:42.877
Exactly.

23:42.901 --> 23:44.684
But that's not the law
in New York, right?

23:44.685 --> 23:47.052
Prosecutors can seek life
without parole

23:47.104 --> 23:49.021
for cop killers,
but it's not mandatory.

23:49.073 --> 23:50.739
Well, it should be.

23:50.825 --> 23:52.169
You don't believe someone
who commits murder

23:52.193 --> 23:54.359
when they're young
can ever be reformed?

23:54.411 --> 23:55.911
What I believe doesn't matter.

23:55.996 --> 23:57.362
What matters is what he did.

23:57.414 --> 23:59.198
That can't be undone.

23:59.250 --> 24:01.566
You kill a cop,
you go to jail forever.

24:01.619 --> 24:03.418
That's right,
and if you get reformed

24:03.504 --> 24:05.454
while you're in prison,
or the church decides

24:05.539 --> 24:07.589
to make you a saint,
well, good for you.

24:07.675 --> 24:10.153
You should still spend the rest
of your life rotting in prison.

24:10.177 --> 24:11.521
Why should the law
be any different

24:11.545 --> 24:12.825
just because the
victim is a cop?

24:14.098 --> 24:17.415
You really gotta ask that
question in this family?

24:17.468 --> 24:19.718
No. Sorry.

24:19.770 --> 24:22.888
No. That's a fair question,
Sean.

24:22.940 --> 24:24.589
Truth is, a cop's life

24:24.642 --> 24:28.110
isn't worth any more
than anyone else's on paper.

24:28.195 --> 24:31.596
But the murder of a police
officer is treated differently.

24:31.649 --> 24:33.098
But if everyone's life is equal,

24:33.150 --> 24:34.461
then why should the law
be any different?

24:34.485 --> 24:37.269
It's not about
the individual, Sean,

24:37.321 --> 24:40.239
it's about the uniform,
what it stands for.

24:41.458 --> 24:42.574
I just don't get it.

24:42.626 --> 24:44.326
(SIGHS)

24:44.411 --> 24:47.462
We choose to live in a
society governed by laws.

24:47.548 --> 24:50.749
And the police symbolize
that choice and those laws.

24:50.801 --> 24:52.729
JAMIE: So when you kill a cop,
it's not just an attack

24:52.753 --> 24:55.170
on a person, it's an attack
on the rule of law.

24:55.256 --> 24:56.805
It's an attack on everyone.

24:56.891 --> 24:58.307
Damn right it is.

24:58.392 --> 25:01.143
In my opinion, you kill
a police officer,

25:01.228 --> 25:03.145
you forfeit the right to live

25:03.230 --> 25:05.964
in a civilized society... ever.

25:06.016 --> 25:07.599
And now we're against mercy?

25:07.651 --> 25:09.184
Of course not.

25:09.270 --> 25:12.855
But there is only one entity
that should have a say in this.

25:12.940 --> 25:16.408
If mercy is to be provided
for Mr. Dean,

25:16.443 --> 25:20.495
the survivors of his victim
need to make that plea.

25:20.581 --> 25:21.980
Like that'll ever happen.

25:22.032 --> 25:26.285
Maybe so... but that's the way
it ought to be.

25:27.421 --> 25:29.037
(QUIETLY):
Yeah.

25:29.123 --> 25:31.039
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING
IN DISTANCE)

25:50.394 --> 25:51.877
Lieutenant Gormley.

25:53.397 --> 25:55.731
(GRUNTS)

25:55.816 --> 25:58.116
How can I help you?

25:58.152 --> 25:59.517
Well, for starters,

25:59.570 --> 26:01.370
you can drop dead.

26:01.455 --> 26:04.856
I understand
and I don't blame you.

26:04.909 --> 26:07.359
Well, I sure as hell blame you.

26:07.411 --> 26:08.577
What are you here for?

26:08.662 --> 26:11.413
Talk about your upcoming
parole hearing.

26:11.498 --> 26:15.867
I did a terrible thing.

26:15.920 --> 26:17.753
You destroyed a family.

26:17.838 --> 26:20.088
I know there's nothing
I can ever do

26:20.174 --> 26:22.174
to ease the pain
I've caused them.

26:22.226 --> 26:24.542
You can withdraw
your parole application

26:24.595 --> 26:28.046
and spend the rest of your life
in here like you deserve.

26:28.098 --> 26:31.316
I have lung cancer.

26:33.687 --> 26:36.355
My son...

26:36.407 --> 26:41.026
has a seven-year-old daughter
I've never met.

26:41.078 --> 26:44.246
I want to spend the time
I have left with them.

26:44.331 --> 26:47.666
Here's the deal.

26:47.701 --> 26:51.336
You executed a cop.

26:51.372 --> 26:53.839
Okay?

26:53.874 --> 26:58.377
You walk out of here,
your life is in danger.

26:58.429 --> 27:00.345
That's not a threat.

27:00.381 --> 27:02.414
That's a fact.

27:02.466 --> 27:05.851
I understand, Lieutenant.

27:05.886 --> 27:08.971
But if the parole board
signs off,

27:09.056 --> 27:11.723
I'm leaving this place.

27:11.775 --> 27:15.060
I'm gonna die a free man.

27:28.742 --> 27:30.459
Hey, Sunday's supposed to be
a day of rest.

27:32.046 --> 27:34.997
I'm just drilling down
on Child Services.

27:35.082 --> 27:38.467
Outcomes for kids like Annie
are pretty lousy.

27:38.552 --> 27:41.119
They all do the
best they can, Eddie.

27:41.171 --> 27:43.255
Yeah, but at the end of the day,
where she ends up

27:43.307 --> 27:45.257
is pretty much a crapshoot.

27:45.309 --> 27:47.392
Okay, well, how many
times have you told me

27:47.428 --> 27:49.728
that you can't
save them all?

27:49.763 --> 27:50.979
About exactly

27:51.065 --> 27:52.814
as many times as you've told me

27:52.900 --> 27:55.100
"I'm just trying
to save this one."

27:55.152 --> 27:59.104
(CHUCKLES): All right.

27:59.156 --> 28:02.824
Well, just so you know,
my answer is yes.

28:02.910 --> 28:04.476
Yes to what?

28:04.528 --> 28:07.946
If you want to look into
adopting this baby,

28:07.998 --> 28:09.448
I'm good with it.

28:09.500 --> 28:11.950
Adopting her?

28:13.087 --> 28:14.819
You and me?

28:14.872 --> 28:16.705
Well, isn't that
what's going on?

28:16.790 --> 28:18.206
At least, in the
back of your mind?

28:18.292 --> 28:21.460
Not in the back or in the front
or anywhere.

28:21.512 --> 28:23.211
Oh.

28:23.297 --> 28:25.180
I misread. Sorry.

28:26.800 --> 28:29.885
Uh, truth be told,
I'm not so sure...

28:29.970 --> 28:31.803
about having kids, period.

28:33.891 --> 28:35.557
Well, that's news to me.

28:35.642 --> 28:38.176
We never really talked
about it.

28:38.228 --> 28:40.011
On account of what happened
with your family?

28:40.064 --> 28:41.679
Hey, I turned out okay.

28:41.732 --> 28:45.183
- Yes, you did.
- That's not the reason.

28:45.235 --> 28:46.868
Okay, what is?

28:46.954 --> 28:50.155
I'm gonna be honest here.

28:50.207 --> 28:53.158
More like what happened
with your family.

28:54.711 --> 28:57.829
Two casualties in one generation
on account of the job.

28:57.881 --> 29:00.916
You put it that way...

29:01.001 --> 29:02.551
I'm not saying, like,
it's a curse,

29:02.636 --> 29:05.703
it's just that I--
we, as cops--

29:05.756 --> 29:07.923
we carry a higher risk
of not coming home one day.

29:08.008 --> 29:09.257
A lot of cops
have kids, Eddie.

29:09.343 --> 29:11.643
I know.

29:11.678 --> 29:14.513
I never say never.

29:14.565 --> 29:16.148
But I'm not much of a gambler.

29:16.183 --> 29:18.900
Re-- I'm really not
my father's daughter.

29:20.687 --> 29:24.556
When I consider the odds
of bringing home

29:24.608 --> 29:26.741
a beautiful little girl
like Annie,

29:26.827 --> 29:28.410
and...

29:28.495 --> 29:33.231
leaving her abandoned there...

29:33.283 --> 29:36.234
I can see down that
rabbit hole, too.

29:36.286 --> 29:37.869
But I'm not going in.

29:46.130 --> 29:48.296
What the hell took so long

29:48.382 --> 29:50.182
to get this River's
address, anyway?

29:50.217 --> 29:52.584
Well, the one he gave us when
we collared him was a phony,

29:52.636 --> 29:54.269
so I had to do
some digging.

29:54.354 --> 29:57.139
I'm not sure why we're sitting
on his place.

29:57.224 --> 29:59.357
Without a new witness
we've got squat

29:59.393 --> 30:00.787
until he goes after
his next victim.

30:00.811 --> 30:02.594
And that's what we're
gonna talk him out of.

30:02.646 --> 30:04.479
- How?
- By telling him

30:04.565 --> 30:06.426
that the next time he tries
to take someone down,

30:06.450 --> 30:07.983
he's gonna have
to answer to me.

30:08.068 --> 30:10.452
Forget it.

30:10.537 --> 30:12.404
He can come after us
for harassment.

30:12.456 --> 30:13.905
Let him.

30:13.957 --> 30:17.742
Look, he needs to understand
that he's the hunted one now.

30:20.297 --> 30:21.913
There he is.

30:24.635 --> 30:25.884
Let's go.

30:25.919 --> 30:27.586
- Danny.
- Come on.

30:45.355 --> 30:47.989
(WHISPERS):
Come on.

30:51.495 --> 30:53.778
♪﻿﻿﻿ ♪

31:08.879 --> 31:10.106
What the hell
are you doing here?

31:10.130 --> 31:11.630
I've been tailing Rivers
all day.

31:11.682 --> 31:12.881
How'd you get
his address?

31:12.966 --> 31:14.216
CJA bail form.

31:14.301 --> 31:16.141
It's their ticket out
so they play it straight.

31:16.186 --> 31:18.186
- Pretty smart.
DANNY: Yeah, pretty smart.

31:18.272 --> 31:19.749
But we'll take it from here.
Good night.

31:19.773 --> 31:21.367
Yeah, I watched Rivers
case his next ATM.

31:21.391 --> 31:22.674
When he makes his
move tonight,

31:22.726 --> 31:24.392
I'm gonna be there
to nail his ass.

31:24.478 --> 31:25.538
No, you're not gonna be there,

31:25.562 --> 31:26.789
because it's our case,
not yours.

31:26.813 --> 31:28.947
I got the same authority
to go after Rivers as you.

31:28.982 --> 31:30.848
Difference is, I'm gonna
do it the right way.

31:31.151 --> 31:32.895
You're gonna back off,
or I'm gonna  <i>make</i> you back off.

31:32.919 --> 31:33.402
- Oh, really?
BAEZ: Stop it!

31:33.718 --> 31:34.652
- Come and make me back off!
- Yeah!

31:34.738 --> 31:36.182
BAEZ: Okay.
- I want to see you make me back off.

31:36.206 --> 31:37.600
I'll make you back up right now!
You gonna make me back off?

31:37.624 --> 31:38.957
Hey, stop it!

31:39.042 --> 31:41.292
This is about nailing Rivers,

31:41.378 --> 31:43.745
so just put 'em back
in your pants and listen.

31:44.998 --> 31:47.131
You're gonna need backup
to take this guy down.

31:47.217 --> 31:49.467
Yeah, maybe.

31:49.553 --> 31:50.780
And Anthony made Rivers'
next target,

31:50.804 --> 31:52.942
so he's gonna be
in charge of this one.

31:52.966 --> 31:54.966
(SCOFFS)

31:55.225 --> 31:56.474
Danny?

31:57.594 --> 31:59.511
Fine. Whatever.

31:59.596 --> 32:01.896
Great. Nice teamwork.

32:12.753 --> 32:14.703
(KEYPAD BEEPING)

32:23.177 --> 32:25.177
You got eyes on Rivers?

32:27.015 --> 32:27.899
BAEZ:
10-4.

32:27.900 --> 32:30.066
You're heading right for him.

32:38.409 --> 32:41.560
(PANTING)

32:41.612 --> 32:43.696
(GRUNTING)

32:44.782 --> 32:46.565
Give me your wallet!

32:46.617 --> 32:48.451
(GRUNTING)

32:48.536 --> 32:49.835
Remember me?

32:50.705 --> 32:53.539
(GRUNTING)

32:54.425 --> 32:55.624
DANNY:
Help me out!

32:55.710 --> 32:56.792
I'm gonna help.
Hell, yeah!

32:56.878 --> 32:57.793
Police!

32:57.879 --> 32:59.762
(GRUNTING)

32:59.847 --> 33:01.097
Hands behind your back!

33:01.182 --> 33:03.716
Ah. Son of a bitch!

33:03.768 --> 33:04.768
(BOTH GRUNT)

33:04.852 --> 33:06.769
Get him up!
Get him on his feet!

33:06.854 --> 33:08.788
You're under arrest.
Son of a bitch!

33:08.856 --> 33:10.272
- Get him out of here!
- Let's go.

33:10.358 --> 33:11.757
Yeah!

33:11.809 --> 33:13.109
(SNIFFLES)

33:13.194 --> 33:15.111
(GROANS)

33:16.197 --> 33:18.314
You okay?

33:18.399 --> 33:20.766
Yeah. What the hell
is in there?

33:20.818 --> 33:22.651
Smells like yesterday's fish.

33:22.737 --> 33:24.787
That coat's
probably had it.

33:24.872 --> 33:27.990
Think-think
that's funny, huh?

33:28.076 --> 33:29.992
Oh, I get it.
You picked this place

33:30.078 --> 33:32.244
'cause you knew
this trash would be here,

33:32.296 --> 33:33.612
and I'd end up like this, huh?

33:33.664 --> 33:36.749
Come on. You think a
dumb square badge like me

33:36.801 --> 33:39.451
could come up with
something like this?

33:39.504 --> 33:41.804
I guess I deserved it, huh?

33:41.889 --> 33:44.423
- Big time.
- Mm-hmm. Thank you.

33:44.475 --> 33:46.642
You were wrong to
screw with the line-up,

33:46.727 --> 33:49.845
but I respect how you stuck with
the case after it went south.

33:49.931 --> 33:51.847
You, too. Tell you what.

33:51.933 --> 33:53.432
How about we process
this jackass,

33:53.484 --> 33:55.300
and I'll buy you
a beer, okay?

33:55.353 --> 33:57.302
Only if you
take a shower.

33:57.355 --> 33:59.271
Okay, deal.

34:05.496 --> 34:07.446
- You went to see Terrence Dean?
- Yeah.

34:07.498 --> 34:09.165
Anything I need to know

34:09.250 --> 34:11.367
regarding possible fallout,
put it in a memo.

34:11.452 --> 34:13.452
Hang on, Garrett. Please.

34:15.172 --> 34:18.541
Look...
I'm sorry for what I said.

34:18.626 --> 34:21.326
- Hey, I'm getting used to it.
-Used to what?

34:21.379 --> 34:23.963
Whenever I offer my opinion
regarding police matters,

34:24.014 --> 34:26.348
you're the first
to remind me I'm not a cop.

34:26.434 --> 34:29.885
Well, look, the fact is,
you never walked a beat.

34:29.971 --> 34:31.887
It's also a fact
that you know nothing

34:31.973 --> 34:33.938
about handling
the New York City press corp.

34:33.975 --> 34:36.641
Do I dismiss
your suggestions out of hand?

34:36.694 --> 34:38.476
Actually, you kind of do.

34:39.614 --> 34:41.530
Okay, fair point.

34:44.318 --> 34:46.185
Do I make you feel like...

34:46.237 --> 34:48.404
you don't even belong
in the room?

34:48.489 --> 34:50.539
No. No, you don't.

34:50.625 --> 34:55.127
When Frank closes his door,
and it's just you, Baker and me,

34:55.163 --> 34:56.911
there's a reason
I'm in that room,

34:56.998 --> 34:59.381
and it's not just
to manage headlines.

34:59.467 --> 35:00.549
I get that.

35:00.635 --> 35:02.134
Do you?

35:02.170 --> 35:04.753
Frank wants an outside opinion.

35:04.839 --> 35:08.424
Someone who  <i>doesn't</i> live
in Copland 24/7.

35:08.509 --> 35:10.726
Someone who's not afraid
to speak up

35:10.811 --> 35:13.062
even when it crosses
that sacred blue line.

35:13.147 --> 35:14.787
Well, you've never been afraid
to do that.

35:14.849 --> 35:17.149
I may not know police procedure
chapter and verse,

35:17.185 --> 35:20.269
but I do know that you seeing
Terrence Dean was wrong.

35:20.354 --> 35:21.854
Tell that to the boss.

35:21.906 --> 35:23.405
- I already did.
- And?

35:23.491 --> 35:24.907
He disagreed... loudly.

35:26.077 --> 35:27.726
But he listened.

35:27.778 --> 35:30.529
That's all I'm asking for.

35:42.710 --> 35:43.737
I heard you're
looking for me.

35:43.761 --> 35:45.077
Yes, but I told your office

35:45.129 --> 35:46.411
I would come to you.

35:46.464 --> 35:48.464
I was in the neighborhood.

35:51.219 --> 35:53.185
(DOOR CLOSES)

35:55.056 --> 35:56.588
So?

35:56.641 --> 35:59.058
I decided not
to go to the mayor.

35:59.110 --> 36:02.261
Figured. I was just trying
to give you a way out.

36:02.313 --> 36:03.862
I know, and I appreciate it,

36:03.898 --> 36:06.282
but going behind my father's
back and playing politics--

36:06.367 --> 36:08.267
that's not who I am.

36:08.319 --> 36:09.768
You played me pretty good.

36:09.820 --> 36:11.120
That was not my intention.

36:13.157 --> 36:14.740
I got in over my head.

36:14.792 --> 36:16.742
So whatever you decide
to fire at me,

36:16.794 --> 36:18.744
please don't gut
the sex-trafficking law.

36:18.796 --> 36:20.329
You'd be hitting
the wrong target.

36:20.414 --> 36:21.780
I wouldn't.

36:21.832 --> 36:23.615
This is just
between you and me.

36:23.668 --> 36:25.117
- Okay.
- Well...

36:25.169 --> 36:27.803
you, me and your old man.

36:27.888 --> 36:30.339
My father didn't walk into this.
I pulled him in.

36:30.424 --> 36:33.142
Well, you got pull, all right.

36:33.227 --> 36:35.460
I sat down with him
this morning.

36:35.513 --> 36:37.313
We traded

36:37.398 --> 36:39.626
over a couple of points,
but he'll be standing next to me

36:39.650 --> 36:41.317
when I roll out
my crime bill next week.

36:42.436 --> 36:44.270
That's news to me.

36:44.322 --> 36:46.522
Maybe you're a better salesman
than you thought.

36:46.607 --> 36:47.990
And you and I?

36:48.075 --> 36:50.359
We're even.

36:50.444 --> 36:52.278
It's a pleasure
doing business with you.

36:56.117 --> 36:57.366
Until the next time.

36:57.451 --> 36:59.251
There won't be a next time.

37:00.338 --> 37:02.288
Never say never.

37:18.055 --> 37:19.504
Hey.

37:19.557 --> 37:21.523
Thanks for coming...
45 minutes late.

37:21.609 --> 37:22.725
Ah, something came up.

37:22.810 --> 37:24.393
You ran the address,
and you found out

37:24.478 --> 37:26.845
it was a rescue shelter, and
you put two and two together?

37:26.897 --> 37:29.732
What I was actually doing
out in the real world

37:29.817 --> 37:31.317
is tracking down
Annie's grandmother,

37:31.369 --> 37:33.070
her next known legal
guardian of record.

37:33.071 --> 37:35.418
I spent hours doing that.
How did you find her?

37:35.442 --> 37:36.790
The phone number was right

37:36.791 --> 37:38.907
in the file, but the
area code was wrong.

37:38.993 --> 37:41.526
It... it took some time,
but she's on a train now,

37:41.579 --> 37:42.911
coming down to
pick her up.

37:42.997 --> 37:44.296
Oh.

37:44.332 --> 37:45.414
You're welcome.

37:45.499 --> 37:47.249
Thank you.

37:47.335 --> 37:49.051
Really. Thank you.

37:49.136 --> 37:51.053
(BARKING)

37:51.138 --> 37:53.205
We're not that couple,
are we?

37:53.257 --> 37:54.406
What couple?

37:54.492 --> 37:56.726
The kind that get a dog
as some kind of dry run

37:56.727 --> 37:58.193
for what kind of
parents they'd be like.

37:58.217 --> 37:59.729
No.

37:59.730 --> 38:01.013
Good.

38:01.065 --> 38:03.015
Never really made sense
to me anyway.

38:03.067 --> 38:07.903
With a dog, you can try out a
few, and you choose, and with...

38:07.988 --> 38:09.905
a baby, they just...

38:09.990 --> 38:12.574
hand you the one that's yours,

38:12.660 --> 38:16.245
and there's no refunds,
no returns.

38:16.330 --> 38:18.914
Never thought about it that way.

38:18.999 --> 38:21.917
You do it,
there's no going back.

38:23.037 --> 38:25.087
So what are we doing here?

38:25.172 --> 38:27.406
I'm letting you in
on a little secret.

38:27.458 --> 38:30.742
Um... I come here
once a month

38:30.795 --> 38:34.096
for a little unconditional love.

38:34.181 --> 38:35.681
(DISTANT BARKING)

38:35.716 --> 38:37.299
(LAUGHING):
Okay.

38:37.385 --> 38:38.917
But we're not
taking him home?

38:38.969 --> 38:41.586
Her. And no.

38:41.639 --> 38:43.922
I'm... I'm not ready

38:43.974 --> 38:45.858
for a full-time dog just yet.

38:47.228 --> 38:48.894
Unless you are.

38:48.946 --> 38:50.729
I could think about that.

38:52.233 --> 38:53.816
But only
if you're 100% on board.

38:53.901 --> 38:55.401
I like that.

38:55.453 --> 38:57.903
I think that's the way
we should think about stuff.

38:57.955 --> 38:59.321
Stuff?

38:59.407 --> 39:02.107
First house, a pet.

39:02.159 --> 39:04.293
A kid, everything.

39:04.378 --> 39:06.245
Always making sure
the other one

39:06.297 --> 39:08.247
is 100% on board.

39:08.299 --> 39:10.382
If we do that,

39:10.418 --> 39:14.420
I think there's no limit
to the life that we can build.

39:16.257 --> 39:18.173
You want to get up here?

39:18.259 --> 39:19.791
Get a little puppy love?

39:19.844 --> 39:21.593
Come on.

39:31.272 --> 39:33.856
Kind of hung me out
to dry there, Dad, didn't you?

39:33.941 --> 39:35.824
Your daughter's here,
Commissioner.

39:35.910 --> 39:38.110
So I hear. Thank you, Baker.

39:39.747 --> 39:41.363
(DOOR CLOSES)

39:42.583 --> 39:44.199
You carved me up

39:44.285 --> 39:45.617
over the governor's crime bill,

39:45.669 --> 39:47.230
and then you go out there
and support it?

39:47.254 --> 39:49.671
Well, it's a little
more complicated than that.

39:49.757 --> 39:51.011
I'm listening.

39:51.012 --> 39:52.962
No, you're not.
You're reloading.

39:55.851 --> 39:57.884
And not that I owe you
an explanation,

39:57.969 --> 40:00.186
but Mendez pulled back
on granting new powers

40:00.272 --> 40:01.888
to the state police.

40:01.973 --> 40:03.223
And why would he do that?

40:03.308 --> 40:05.642
Quid pro quo.

40:05.694 --> 40:08.027
He needs my support.

40:08.113 --> 40:11.064
And why didn't you suggest that
when I came to  <i>you</i> for support?

40:11.149 --> 40:14.534
Because when I make deals,
it's to advance the interests

40:14.619 --> 40:18.872
of the NYPD, not to bail
my children out of trouble.

40:20.458 --> 40:22.375
I guess I had that coming.

40:22.460 --> 40:24.694
And then some.

40:24.746 --> 40:27.330
So besides winning
a few concessions,

40:27.382 --> 40:30.083
how did you advance
the interests of the NYPD?

40:30.168 --> 40:32.502
That would be need-to-know.

40:32.554 --> 40:33.837
I need to know.

40:37.893 --> 40:39.843
Not to leave this room.

40:39.895 --> 40:41.761
But the parole board was set

40:41.847 --> 40:44.731
to release Mr. Dean
first thing Monday morning.

40:44.816 --> 40:47.183
That will no longer happen.

40:49.321 --> 40:52.388
The parole board is supposed
to be independent.

40:52.440 --> 40:55.859
And cop killers are supposed
to die in jail.

40:55.911 --> 40:58.945
Only if they were sentenced
to do so, and Dean wasn't.

40:59.030 --> 41:01.364
Oh, come on, Erin.
He got 25 to life,

41:01.416 --> 41:03.533
so parole is a judgment call.

41:03.585 --> 41:05.251
Yes, but not your judgment.

41:05.337 --> 41:08.588
No, but sound judgment...
by any measure.

41:12.844 --> 41:15.094
I'm just grateful
to be square with Mendez

41:15.180 --> 41:17.413
and off the hook for any favors.

41:17.465 --> 41:19.515
Except for the one you owe me.

